  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then Asa was wroth with the seer,.... For this faithful reproof of him, which was another instance of his sin and folly: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and put him in a prison house; in a very strait place, in which he could not turn himself, what we call \"little ease\"; some say it was the stocks, others a pillory he put him into: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for he was in a rage with him because of this thing; his passion rose very high, and to which he gave way, and was his infirmity: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Asa oppressed some of the people the same time; by fines and imprisonments, such as perhaps expressed their disapprobation of his league with the king of Syria, and of his ill usage of the prophet. ",
        "children": [
